Market Analysis and Insights

Biometrics as a Service Market

Biometrics as a service market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the market to reach at an estimated value of USD 3.0 billion by 2029 and grow at a CAGR of 9.65% in the above-mentioned forecast period.

Biometrics-as-a-service (also referred as BaaS) is basically a cloud-based application which is able to identify and authenticate individuals on the basis of their biological and behavioral characteristics. Generally, it is based on biometrics technology which records the userâ€™s presence by highly accurate eye, voice and facial recognition, which apparently helps in enhancing the security of the existing organizational infrastructure.

The factors such as increased use of mobile devices and threats caused due to high security are expected to emerge as the significant factors accelerating the growth of biometrics as a service market in the above-mentioned forecast period. In addition to this, its advantages such as more secure than traditional forms of entry of codes like pin, passwords and locks, among others will further aggravate the growth of the biometrics as a service market. However, the factors such as security of biometric data on cloud storage and involvement of high cost for the biometric technologies results as a growth restraint for the market.

The increasing use of digital platforms for transactions is anticipated to generate lucrative opportunities for the biometrics as a service market. On the other hand, the integration of biometric infrastructure into the existing systems will pose as a challenge for the biometrics as a service market.

